rComments: I thought ethics would be a useless and boring class but he made ethics so applicable to everyday nursing practice! Lectures were interesting and useful. If you completed the assignments and put in some effort in it's not hard to get great marks.

I took this class a year ago and absolutely loved it! David made me appreciate nursing far more than I already had! This was one of my favourite classes in the nursing program. I learned so much and still read the 'textbook' that was assigned. The exam was a bit difficult, but if you study and do the reading the readings it's not too bad.

Hes very nice but ethics is boring and he made it even worse. Practice exam nothing like the final. Final exam had terms and theories never discussed in class. Being a good nurse does not make a good prof.

He is very nice and clearly cares about nursing as a profession. However; his exams were incredibly unclear. He gave practice exams that was nothing like the real exam and focused questions on content from previous years that he did not teach this year and clearly reused questions. Teaches undergrads like PHD students.

Very articulate, and clearly cares about the wellbeing of his students. Class content was often vague but exam was fair. The course itself is somewhat disorganized, but his lectures are worth listening to. He is fairly clear about expectations if you just ask.

Overall, this professor is knowledgeable and  passionate. Although, the assignments are very misleading due to what the teacher expects from the student. Very rude at times when voicing his opinion about your own work (felt unqualified) and does not mark fairly. One-on-one with the student this prof needs to work on his empathy and compassion.

1st paper was graded by him & the TA, 2nd paper marked externally and the criteria for these papers was ambiguous at best. Although you sense David cares deeply about the subject matter and his students, his teaching style falls short of  usefulness or applicability. Answers questions outside of class, feedback isn't very useful, records lectures.
